	<fdd:identificationAndDescription>
		<fdd:fullName>AVI (Audio Video Interleaved) with Cinepak Video Codec</fdd:fullName>
		<fdd:keywords>
			<fdd:keyword>video formats</fdd:keyword>
			<fdd:keyword>AVI</fdd:keyword>
		</fdd:keywords>
		<fdd:description>File format that wraps a Cinepak video bitstream with other data chunks, e.g., audio, in an AVI wrapper.  Multiple versions of Cinepak exist, including  <i>SuperMac</i>, <i>Radius</i>, and <i>Compression Technologies</i>; this document does not distinguish between them.</fdd:description>
		<fdd:shortDescription>File format that wraps a Cinepak video bitstream with other data chunks, e.g., audio., in an AVI wrapper. </fdd:shortDescription>
		<fdd:productionPhase>Used as a middle-state and/or final-state format for enduser delivery. </fdd:productionPhase>
